        <instrument_host_desc>
 
      Mt Bigelow 61-inch Kuiper Telescope
      ===================================
      Mt. Bigelow (elevation 8230 ft/2510 m) is part of the Steward
      Observatory Catalina site, located north of Tucson, AZ and operated
      by the University of Arizona.  The following information is quoted
      from this website:
 
         http://james.as.arizona.edu/~psmith/61inch
 
      as it appeared in 21 November 2005.
 
        Telescope &amp; Site
        ----------------
 
        Elevation:        2510m = 8230ft
        Latitude:         +32 24.0&apos; 59.3&apos;&apos; N
        Longitude:        110 44&apos; 04.3&apos;&apos; W
               These coordinates are accurate to about 1&apos;&apos;.
        Time zone:        +7 hours
 
        Primary Mirror Diameter:  1.54m = 61 inches
 
        f/13.5 Cassegrain focus:
            Plate Scale: 100 microns/arcsec = 10.0 arcsec/mm (nominal)
            Useful Field of View: &gt;435 arcsec diameter
            Secondary Diameter: 40.96 cm
        f/45 Cassegrain focus
            Plate Scale: 351 microns/arcsec = 2.85 arcsec/mm (nominal)
            Useful Field of View: &gt;325 arcsec diameter
            Secondary Diameter: 14.5 cm
 
        Typical Seeing: 1-2&apos;&apos;

        </instrument_host_desc>
        <instrument_host_id>MTBG61</instrument_host_id>
